# Release version sync (Camera Wall + go2rtc)

## The bug we must not repeat

GitHub release tag `v1.2.5` was published while `desktop/electron-viewer/package.json` stayed at `1.2.4`.  
The update API reported **1.2.5 available**, but the installer asset was still **1.2.4** — Camera Wall offered a fake upgrade and reinstalled the same version.

## Before every `git tag vX.Y.Z`

1. **`desktop/electron-viewer/package.json`** — set `"version": "X.Y.Z"` to **match the tag** (always, for every release that runs CI — not only when Electron code changed).
2. **`internal/viewer/about.go`** — bump `ViewerUIVersion` when `www/viewer/**` changed.
3. **Tag name** — `vX.Y.Z` must match both go2rtc `-ldflags` version (CI) and desktop `package.json`.
4. **After CI** — verify release assets: installer filename contains `X.Y.Z` and `/api/viewer/desktop/update` returns `"version":"X.Y.Z"` (from installer filename, not tag alone).

## API rule (implemented)

`viewer.desktop.github` update JSON must use **installer filename version**, not GitHub tag, when they differ. Electron client also cross-checks `download_url` filename.

## Do not

- Push a release tag without syncing `package.json`.
- Report a desktop update as available when installer semver ≤ installed app version.
- Assume tag version equals installer version — always check the `.exe` name on the release.

See [docs/RELEASE_CI.md](docs/RELEASE_CI.md) and `.cursor/rules/patch-releases.mdc`.
